President Obama announced several key additions to the Office of the White House Counsel. The appointees include Deputy Counsels, Special Counsel, Associate Counsels, Deputy Associate Counsels, Research Director, and Staff Assistants and Administrative Assistants. The President emphasized the importance of ethics and transparency in government and expressed confidence that the appointees would serve the American people well. Some notable appointees include Daniel Meltzer, Mary DeRosa, Neal Wolin, and Norman L. Eisen.